            <title>[CAMEL-3493] ConcurrentModificationException in DefaultCamelContext.removeRouteDefinitions()</title>
                <link>https://issues.apache.org/jira/browse/CAMEL-3493</link>
                <project id="12311211" key="CAMEL">Camel</project>
                    <description>&lt;p&gt;I get the following exception in DefaultCamelContext.removeRouteDefinitions().  We are removing route definitions from multiple threads.  I see synchronization in various other methods, but not this one. &lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;Caused by: java.util.ConcurrentModificationException&lt;br/&gt;
	at java.util.AbstractList$Itr.checkForComodification(AbstractList.java:372)&lt;br/&gt;
	at java.util.AbstractList$Itr.next(AbstractList.java:343)&lt;br/&gt;
	at java.util.AbstractCollection.removeAll(AbstractCollection.java:336)&lt;br/&gt;
	at org.apache.camel.impl.DefaultCamelContext.removeRouteDefinitions(DefaultCamelContext.java:588)&lt;/p&gt;</description>
